original: Liljenström, Gustaf Robert, provin-sial- o. sjukstuguläkare, Rejmyra, f. 16/7/92 i Ulricehamn av apot. Gottfrid L. o. EHn Wahlberg. G. 30 m. Svea Bengtson. Barn: Gunnar f. 32, Monica 36, Nils-Ake o. Gunilla 42. — Studiex. 10 o. med. kand. 21 i Upps., med. lic. i Sthlm 27. E. läk. v. Upps. hosp. 25, assist :läk. o. tf. und :läk. v. Karlshamns las. 27-29, kortare förordn. som provrläk. i Rejmyre distr., und:-läk. v. barnsjukh. Samariten, andre las :underläk. i Kalmar, e. prov:läk. i Degerfors distr. samt som prov:läk. i Stensele distr. 29, tf. stadsläk. i Tidaholm 29-30, tf. prov :läk. i Hjo distr. 31, i Kristianstads distr. 31-32 i Heby o. Teckomatorps distr. 32, tf. las :läk. i Kisa, Finspång o. Haparanda tills, nio mån. 30-33, tf. proviläk. i Njut- ångers distr. 33-34, tf. andre und :läk. v. Stora Ekebergs sanat. 34, därjämte ett flertal kortare förordn. som prov:-läk. o. las:underläk. Civil läkrstip. av första kl. sex mån. 35, prov:- o. sjuk-stuguläk. i Reijmyre distr. sed. 35.
translated: Liljenström, Gustaf Robert, provincial and hospital physician, Rejmyra, born on July 16, 1892 in Ulricehamn to pharmacist Gottfrid L. and EHn Wahlberg. Married on January 30, 1920 to Svea Bengtson. Children: Gunnar, born in 1932, Monica in 1936, Nils-Ake and Gunilla in 1942. Studied and obtained a Bachelor's degree in Medicine in 1921 at Uppsala University, becoming a licensed doctor in Stockholm in 1927. Started as a physician at Uppsala Hospital in 1925, worked as an assistant doctor and acting deputy physician at Karlshamn Hospital from 1927 to 1929, had shorter appointments as a provisional physician in Rejmyre district, and an understudy physician at Samariten Children's Hospital, second deputy physician in Kalmar, a provisional physician in Degerfors district, and another provisional physician in Stensele district in 1929. Acted as a temporary town physician in Tidaholm from 1929 to 1930, temporary provisional physician in Hjo district in 1931, in Kristianstad district from 1931 to 1932, in Heby and Teckomatorp districts in 1932, temporary hospital physician in Kisa, Finspång, and Haparanda for a total of nine months from 1930 to 1933, temporary provisional physician in Njutånger district from 1933 to 1934, temporary second understudy physician at Stora Ekebergs sanatorium in 1934, as well as several shorter appointments as a provisional physician and hospital understudy physician. Awarded a civil medical scholarship of first class for six months in 1935, became a provisional and hospital physician in Rejmyre district since then.
